  .lang.lang-en
    h1 About
    h1 DANUBEPARKS STEP2.0 Project

    p
      strong Anchoring the Danube River Network of Protected Areas as Platform for Preservation of Danube Natural Heritage
    p The project is financed by ETC-SEE (European Territorial Cooperation, South-East Europe) Programme, with its priority axis on “Protection and Improvement of the Environment” and the Area of Intervention “Promote cooperation in management of natural assets and protected areas”.
    p The focus of DANUBEPARKS STEP 2.0 Project is to build on the achievements of the first joint project, anchor results firmly either by implementation actions or by integrating them into a policy framework and to further enlarge the network. The areas of work are River Morphology, Habitat Management, Flagship Species, Monitoring and Anchoring of the Network. 
